-- Tora Prison Hospital Ready to Receive Mubarak, Al-Ahram Reports
-- B y   T a r e k   E l - T a b l a w y
-- 2012-04-17T07:17:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/tora-prison-hospital-ready-to-receive-mubarak-al-ahram-reports.html
Egypt ’s interior minister said
renovations at Cairo’s Tora Prison hospital have been completed
and the facility is ready to receive ousted President  Hosni Mubarak , the state-run Al-Ahram newspaper reported today.  Interior Minister Mohamed Ibrahim said construction company
Arab Contractors had completed the upgrades and other work on
the facility, and officials were waiting for a court order to
move Mubarak there. Mubarak’s two sons and several other top
officials from the ousted regime are being held at the prison,
located on Cairo’s outskirts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tarek El-Tablawy in Cairo at 
 teltablawy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  